description: This is robusta coffee from the Fazenda Cazengo farm and a number of the outlying small holder farmers in the region from 2013 harvest. name: Andrew Hetzel
description: This coffee is RKR (Robusta Kaapi Royale) grade robusta coffee carefully prepared at the Sethuraman Estates farm and wet mill in Magundi, Karnataka India. Sethuraman RKR is exceptionally sweet, has a light and delicate acidity and very little presence of robusta bitterness. We highly recommend this coffee for adding a bold, creamy body to espresso blends and it is one of the few robustas that can also be enjoyed as a single origin drop coffee or espresso.

description: This coffee is a natural sun-dried coffee (known within India as "cherry") carefully prepared at the Sethuraman Estates farm and wet mill in Magundi, Karnataka India.  This year's robusta natural has a substantial body with round mouthfeel and strong but not overpowering and very well-balanced stone fruit-like aroma and flavor of bitter chocolate.
